{"id": "EUVD-2026-2247", "enisaUuid": "23e93b3c-d862-3ba0-9e85-9e5e63109e8b", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nnet: rose: fix invalid array index in rose_kill_by_device()\n\nrose_kill_by_device() collects sockets into a local array[] and then\niterates over them to disconnect sockets bound to a device being brought\ndown.\n\nThe loop mistakenly indexes array[cnt] instead of array[i]. For cnt <\nARRAY_SIZE(array), this reads an uninitialized entry; for cnt ==\nARRAY_SIZE(array), it is an out-of-bounds read. Either case can lead to\nan invalid socket pointer dereference and also leaks references taken\nvia sock_hold().\n\nFix the index to use i.", "datePublished": "2026-01-13T15:34:49", "dateUpdated": "2026-01-13T15:34:49", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-71086", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/1418c12cd3bba79dc56b57b61c99efe40f579981", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/6595beb40fb0ec47223d3f6058ee40354694c8e4", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/92d900aac3a5721fb54f3328f1e089b44a861c38", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/9f6185a32496834d6980b168cffcccc2d6b17280", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/b409ba9e1e63ccf3ab4cc061e33c1f804183543e"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-71086", "GHSA-mqvv-vjpm-cprh"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "1a2dcfa9-bbb2-32e6-af8d-94737172b7cb", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "64b8bc7d5f1434c636a40bdcfcd42b278d1714be <92d900aac3a5721fb54f3328f1e089b44a861c38"}, {"id": "1e820680-3fef-3e92-8f90-48bdb67cceb3", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "64b8bc7d5f1434c636a40bdcfcd42b278d1714be <6595beb40fb0ec47223d3f6058ee40354694c8e4"}, {"id": "27a8c8d9-b35a-379d-b019-1bd54f87a62f", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.1.160"}, {"id": "2dc1f318-c007-3f83-a6bc-27b6d78dff42", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.6.120"}, {"id": "3af0cd33-ddf0-3c5f-9b3e-d3032c22cac6"